headline.main: CANADA.; Prorogation of Proviusial Parliament--Civic Entertainments--Anniversary of the St. Jenn Baptiste Society.

docs.lead_paragraph: On Thursday last the Provincial Parliament was prorogued. Mr. HINCKS stated on be half of Government that this step was preliminary to dissolution. The Ministry had been previously defeated on the answer to the. Governor General's speech.

docs.lead_paragraph: Rev. ROBERT PATTERSON, of Ireland, who accompanied Rev. Dr. DUFF through the West, has accepted a call to the Reformed Presbyterian Church, Cincinnati. Rev. WM. R. CHAPMAN was dismissed, at his own request, from the charge of the church in Aurora, N. Y., at the late session of the Cayuga Presbytery.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE SWINE ORDINANCE.--The Board of Health have extended the swine law so as to prevent the keeping of swine between the 3d of July and 1st of October in any portion of the Eighth and Ninth Wards. The swine in the city of Williamsburg are mostly owned by the Irish, and they threaten to resist the enforcement of the law.
